      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BUSH BOUQUET (2) is a last start placegetter in a Grade 5, jumping from this box and finishing one length away in second over 350m at this track. Goes very well from this same draw winning two races. Has good early burn and drawn to be prominent early off a low draw. Worth another chance. GENOVESE (1) is struggling to break through but racing consistently, finishing in the minors four starts on end. Last time out flew the lids with a fast early sectional but gathered in and finished in the minors when third (20.10) at Grafton over 350m. Reliable out of the boxes and should take advantage of the inside draw. Must be included in calculations. BY A MIRACLE (3) settled down midfield and held her position to the line when finishing 5th (19.27) at this track. Smart beginner who should take advantage of the low draw. A forward showing wouldn't surprise. IN ABSENTIA (4) must be included in main hopes on latest effort.",
